%description:
Regression test for D4 (workstream D, architecture decoupling): ~LinkStateRouting becomes
lifecycle-aware (extends RoutingProtocolBase instead of a plain SimpleModule), so a node
shutdown/restart properly stops/resumes its flooding activity and recomputes its peer
snapshot from the current ~Ted state, instead of silently staying half-initialized (the
pre-D4 bug: the module never noticed the node had been stopped and restarted, kept a stale
peerIfAddrs snapshot taken at simulation start, and never re-announced).

Built on the shipped examples/mpls/testte_failure2 network (RSVPTE4) and its own
scenario.xml, which already shuts down LSR4 at t=2s and restarts it at t=4s -- exactly the
scenario this fix targets. (Manual before/after comparison on this exact network+scenario
showed the pre-D4 code delivering only 348/10000 UDP echo replies after the restart, vs.
9933/10000 with this fix -- LSR4's restart previously left the network's return path mostly
black-holed for the rest of the run; this is a functional bug fix, not just a cosmetic one.)

Asserted, in order:
  1. no ~LinkStateRouting activity at all on LSR4 while it is down (t in [2s, 4s)) -- proves
     incoming floods aren't processed and the module doesn't spuriously tick while stopped;
  2. a fresh "announce" self-message fires on LSR4's ~LinkStateRouting at/after the restart
     (t >= 4s) -- proves handleStartOperation() recomputes peers and reschedules flooding on
     every (re)start, not just once at time 0;
  3. at least one neighbor actually receives a LinkStateMsg flood at/after the restart --
     proves the reflood is observed downstream, not just scheduled locally;
  4. the RSVP-TE LSP still establishes end to end, and host traffic is delivered
     (packetReceived:count > 0) -- proves the restart doesn't break signaling/forwarding;
  5. standard undisposed-object postrun guard -- proves clean teardown, no crash.

%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%inifile: test.ini

[General]
ned-path = ../../../../examples;../../../../src
network = inet.examples.mpls.testte_failure2.RSVPTE4
sim-time-limit = 6s
total-stack = 64MiB
record-vector-results = false
cmdenv-express-mode = false
**.cmdenv-log-level = "info"
output-scalar-file = "${resultdir}/${configname}-#${runnumber}.sca"

**.host1.numApps = 1
**.host1.app[0].typename = "UdpBasicApp"
**.host1.app[0].localPort = 100
**.host1.app[0].destPort = 100
**.host1.app[0].messageLength = 128 bytes
**.host1.app[0].sendInterval = 0.01s
**.host1.app[0].destAddresses = "host3"

**.host3.numApps = 1
**.host3.app[0].typename = "UdpEchoApp"
**.host3.app[0].localPort = 100

**.LSR1.classifier.config = xmldoc("../../../../examples/mpls/testte_failure2/LSR1_fec.xml")
**.LSR1.rsvp.traffic = xmldoc("../../../../examples/mpls/testte_failure2/LSR1_rsvp.xml")

**.LSR*.rsvp.helloInterval = 0.2s
**.LSR*.rsvp.helloTimeout = 0.5s

**.LSR1.peers = "ppp0 ppp1"
**.LSR2.peers = "ppp0 ppp1 ppp2"
**.LSR3.peers = "ppp0 ppp1 ppp2"
**.LSR4.peers = "ppp0 ppp1 ppp2"
**.LSR5.peers = "ppp0 ppp3 ppp4"
**.LSR6.peers = "ppp0 ppp1"
**.LSR7.peers = "ppp0 ppp1"

**.ppp[*].queue.typename = "DropTailQueue"
**.ppp[*].queue.packetCapacity = 10

*.*.hasStatus = true
# reuse the shipped scenario verbatim: <shutdown module="LSR4"/> at t=2s, <startup .../> at t=4s
**.scenarioManager.script = xmldoc("../../../../examples/mpls/testte_failure2/scenario.xml")

%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%# 1. no LinkStateRouting activity at all on LSR4 while it's down ([2s, 4s))
%postrun-command: awk '/^\*\* Event #/ { if (match($0, /t=([0-9.]+)/, m)) t = m[1]+0 } /in RSVPTE4\.LSR4\.linkStateRouting/ && t >= 2 && t < 4 { print "UNEXPECTED_ACTIVITY_WHILE_DOWN:", $0 }' test.out > down_activity.out
%not-contains: down_activity.out
UNEXPECTED_ACTIVITY_WHILE_DOWN
%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%# 2. a fresh "announce" self-message fires on LSR4's LinkStateRouting at/after the restart
%postrun-command: awk '/^\*\* Event #/ { if (match($0, /t=([0-9.]+)/, m)) t = m[1]+0 } /on announce \(omnetpp::cMessage\)  in RSVPTE4\.LSR4\.linkStateRouting/ && t >= 4 { print "POST_RESTART_ANNOUNCE_SCHEDULED:", $0 }' test.out > restart_announce.out
%contains: restart_announce.out
POST_RESTART_ANNOUNCE_SCHEDULED
%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%# 3. a neighbor actually receives a LinkStateMsg flood at/after the restart
%postrun-command: awk '/^\*\* Event #/ { if (match($0, /t=([0-9.]+)/, m)) t = m[1]+0 } /received LINK_STATE message from/ && t >= 4 { print "POST_RESTART_FLOOD_SEEN_AT_NEIGHBOR:", t }' test.out > restart_flood.out
%contains: restart_flood.out
POST_RESTART_FLOOD_SEEN_AT_NEIGHBOR
%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%# 4. the LSP still establishes and traffic is still delivered end to end across the restart
%contains: stdout
Path successfully established
%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%postrun-command: grep "packetReceived:count" results/General-#0.sca | awk '$NF > 0 { print "DELIVERED", $0 }' > delivered.out
%contains: delivered.out
DELIVERED
%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%# 5. clean teardown, no crash
%postrun-command: grep "undisposed object:" test.out > test_undisposed.out || true
%not-contains: test_undisposed.out
undisposed object: (
%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
